---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
---
<Layout
  title="Services — Inguz Care"
  description="Therapeutic, relationship-based residential care with clear routines and close partnership working."
>
  <section class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold">Our Services</h1>
    <p class="mt-4 text-lg max-w-3xl">
      At Inguz Care, we provide nurturing, stable homes for children and young people who need
      safety, consistency and a trusted team around them. Our approach blends therapeutic,
      relationship-based care with clear routines, meaningful activities and close partnership
      with families, schools and professionals.
    </p>

    <!-- Who we support -->
    <div class="mt-10">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold">Who we support</h2>
      <ul class="mt-3 list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
        <li>Children and young people who need a safe, caring home with 24/7 support</li>
        <li>Those who may have experienced loss, trauma or disrupted attachments</li>
        <li>Those who may have additional needs (e.g., social, emotional, mental health or neurodiversity)</li>
        <li>Young people who benefit from predictable routines, individual goals and gentle, consistent care</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <!-- How we care -->
    <div class="mt-10">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold">How we care</h2>

      <div class="mt-4 grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
        <article class="rounded-2xl border p-6">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold">Therapeutic, trauma-informed practice</h3>
          <p class="mt-2">
            We prioritise relationships, regulation and reflection. Staff use calm, consistent responses
            and proactive de-escalation so children feel safe and understood.
          </p>
        </article>

        <article class="rounded-2xl border p-6">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold">Individual plans</h3>
          <p class="mt-2">
            Every child has a personalised care plan with clear goals, co-created with the child and their network.
            We listen, adapt and celebrate progress.
          </p>
        </article>

        <article class="rounded-2xl border p-6">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold">Education at the heart</h3>
          <p class="mt-2">
            We work closely with schools and education partners to support attendance, learning and confidence,
            including tailored pathways where appropriate.
          </p>
        </article>

        <article class="rounded-2xl border p-6">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold">Health &amp; wellbeing</h3>
          <p class="mt-2">
            We coordinate day-to-day health needs and, where appropriate, arrange access to specialist support
            (for example, play or art therapy) through local services.
          </p>
        </article>

        <article class="rounded-2xl border p-6">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold">Family &amp; network work</h3>
          <p class="mt-2">
            We keep children connected to the people who matter to them, facilitating contact sensitively and
            working as one team around the child.
          </p>
        </article>

        <article class="rounded-2xl border p-6">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold">Identity, culture &amp; voice</h3>
          <p class="mt-2">
            We respect culture, beliefs and preferences, and actively include children in decisions that affect their lives.
          </p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Day to day -->
    <div class="mt-10">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold">What life looks like day-to-day</h2>
      <ul class="mt-3 list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
        <li>Warm bedrooms children can personalise, and welcoming shared spaces</li>
        <li>Predictable routines for mornings, mealtimes, study and downtime</li>
        <li>Activities that build skills and confidence: sports, arts, outdoor time and community connections</li>
        <li>Positive behaviour support focused on strengths, safety and the least-restrictive options</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <!-- Placement options -->
    <div class="mt-10">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold">Placement options</h2>
      <p class="mt-2">Subject to assessment and availability at our Radcliffe home:</p>
      <ul class="mt-3 list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
        <li>Planned admissions (short-, medium- or longer-term)</li>
        <li>Emergency admissions considered on a case-by-case basis</li>
        <li>Step-down and transitions planning toward family, foster care or semi-independence</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <!-- Outcomes -->
    <div class="mt-10">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold">Outcomes we focus on</h2>
      <ul class="mt-3 list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
        <li>Feeling safe, settled and listened to</li>
        <li>School engagement and progress</li>
        <li>Emotional regulation and stronger relationships</li>
        <li>Practical life skills and increased independence</li>
        <li>Stability and positive, lasting connections</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <!-- CTA -->
    <div class="mt-12 rounded-xl bg-[#eef5f4] p-6">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold">Referrals &amp; enquiries</h2>
      <p class="mt-2">
        We’re opening soon in Radcliffe, Greater Manchester. To discuss a placement, request our Statement of Purpose,
        or arrange a visit when we open, please contact us on the Contact Us page.
      </p>
      <a
        href="/contact"
        class="mt-4 inline-block px-5 py-3 rounded-lg bg-[#5f7c7b] text-white font-semibold hover:bg-[#3d5756]"
      >
        Contact us
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
